SIMPLE: churlish
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Churlish
<hw>Churl"ish</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Like a churl; rude;
cross-grained; ungracious; surly; illiberal; niggardly.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Churlish</xex> benefits.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Ld.
Burleigh.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Half mankind maintain a <qex>churlish</qex> strife.</q>
<rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Wanting pliancy; unmanageable; unyielding; not
easily wrought; <as>as, a <ex>churlish</ex> soil; the <ex>churlish</ex>
and intractable nature of some minerals</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Boyle.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Churlishly</ent>⟦br⟧
